                <note rend="inline" type="source">FileNo.760d.62/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-28T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 30, 11.34 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s 1392, undated [December 21, 3 p.m.] referring to Legation’s despatch
                    1492, November 18. The German-Finnish agreement was to remain in force until the
                    conclusion of a general peace. It was accepted by delegates of Finland with full
                    powers on October [March?] 7, 1918, but many of the provisions were never fully
                    put in force on account of the changing fortunes of war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MIN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
